{"first_name":"Tim","last_name":"Armstrong","permalink":"tim-armstrong","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/tim-armstrong","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"AOL","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":"","created_at":"Thu Jun 05 19:30:36 UTC 2008","updated_at":"Wed May 25 17:47:03 UTC 2011","overview":"<p>Tim Armstrong was appointed CEO and Chairman of <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/aol\" title=\"AOL\">AOL</a> in March 2009.</p>\n\n<p>Before becoming the CEO of AOL, Armstrong presided over <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/google\" title=\"Google\">Google</a>&#8217;s North American and Latin American advertising sales and operations teams. His team provided customers with local partnerships as well as centralized sales and services. They worked with some of the world&#8217;s most widely recognized brands and advertising agencies in addition to some of the fastest growing medium-sized companies.</p>\n\n<p>Armstrong joined Google from Snowball.com, where he was vice president of sales and strategic partnerships. Prior to his role at Snowball.com, he served as director of integrated sales &amp; marketing at Starwave&#8217;s and <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/walt-disney-internet-group\" title=\"Disney\">Disney</a>&#8217;s ABC/ESPN Internet Ventures, working across the companies&#8217; Internet, TV, radio, and print properties. He started his career by co-founding and running a newspaper based in Boston, MA, before joining <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/idg\" title=\"IDG\">IDG</a> to launch their first consumer Internet magazine, I-Way.</p>\n\n<p>Armstrong is an investor in <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/patch\" title=\"Patch\">Patch</a> and sits on the boards of the Interactive Advertising Bureau (IAB), the Advertising Council, and the Advertising Research Foundation. He is a graduate of and trustee at both Lawrence Academy and Connecticut College, where he earned a double major in economics and sociology.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[120,150],"assets/images/resized/0003/7867/37867v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[200,250],"assets/images/resized/0003/7867/37867v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[360,450],"assets/images/resized/0003/7867/37867v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":"<p>AOL</p>"},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"Bachelor of Science","subject":"Economics and Sociology","institution":"Connecticut College","graduated_year":1995,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null}],"relationships":[{"is_past":false,"title":"Chairman & CEO","firm":{"name":"AOL","permalink":"aol","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,84],"assets/images/resized/0000/4003/4003v5-max-150x150.png"],[[174,98],"assets/images/resized/0000/4003/4003v5-max-250x250.png"],[[174,98],"assets/images/resized/0000/4003/4003v5-max-450x450.png"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"Investor","firm":{"name":"Patch","permalink":"patch","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,59],"assets/images/resized/0003/7355/37355v2-max-150x150.png"],[[218,87],"assets/images/resized/0003/7355/37355v2-max-250x250.png"],[[218,87],"assets/images/resized/0003/7355/37355v2-max-450x450.png"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"Board Member","firm":{"name":"Ladies Who Launch","permalink":"ladies-who-launch","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,47],"assets/images/resized/0002/0080/20080v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[207,65],"assets/images/resized/0002/0080/20080v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[207,65],"assets/images/resized/0002/0080/20080v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":true,"title":"President, The Americas Operation and Senior Vice President, Advertising Sales and Operations","firm":{"name":"Google","permalink":"google","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,51],"assets/images/resized/0002/9578/29578v31-max-